festival.introText:
Birmingham's dedicated metal festival returns for a 14th year!

 

Originally planned as a one-off event, overwhelming demand from fans has led Hammerfest to grow from strength to strength, and it is now a firm fixture on the metalhead's calendar.

 

Previous face-melting headliners include Napalm Death, Paradise Lost and Skindred, and this year sees Finnish legends Lordi step up to the plate to get the pit sweating. Unmissable!

faqs.question: When is Hammerfest 2023?
faqs.answer: Hammerfest takes place on Saturday 11th February and Sunday 12th February 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to Hammerfest by car?
faqs.answer: The postcode for Sat Nav is B1 1DB. The venue doesn't have official parking but there is street parking and bays on Bow Street and Irving Street nearby. There are also nearby car parks with accessible spaces - please ensure you display your blue badge if you use these.

faqs.question: Does Hammerfest have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Hammerfest is a non-camping festival so camping equipment is not needed. There are hotels nearby within walking distance.

faqs.question: Accessibility information
faqs.answer: For the most up to date advice on accessibility, please phone 0207 193 1845 before making your booking to ensure the venue can accommodate your needs.

faqs.question: Where is Hammerfest?
faqs.answer:
Hammerfest is located at O2 Academy, Birmingham

16-18 Horsefair

Birmingham

B1 1DB

faqs.question: How do I get to Hammerfest by train?
faqs.answer: O2 Academy Birmingham is only about 500 metres away from Birmingham New Street station.

faqs.question: Does Hammerfest have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Hammerfest. You will need to bring photo ID.

faqs.question: How do I get to Hammerfest by bus/coach?
faqs.answer: Please see https://hammerfest.co.uk/information/ for the most up to date information.

faqs.question: Will there be alcohol at the event?
faqs.answer: Alcohol will be served the whole time the arenas are open. If you do drink, don’t drive – everything on site is within walking distance.

faqs.question: Is there anywhere I can get internet access?
faqs.answer: There are free Wi-Fi hotspots on site, in the arena areas.
